cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with automatic art analysis using computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of context-aware embeddings to enhance visual representations, which involves the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed models in several art analysis problems, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of multi-task learning and knowledge graphs further supports the inclusion of this paper in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of images, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
